  "body": "### Description\r\nAs a node operator, I want to configure TCP and UDP p2p traffic to use different ports to make configuration in a Kubernetes environment easier.\r\n\r\n### Acceptance Criteria\r\n* Teku provides configuration options to independently specify different ports for UDP and TCP p2p traffic\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\nTeku's `--p2p-port` option sets the port number for both UDP and TCP to the same value. We can leave this behaviour as-is but add `--p2p-port-tcp` and `--p2p-port-udp` options that override the `--p2p-port` option or default.\r\n\r\nWe may also need to add `--p2p-advertised-port-tcp` and `--p2p-advertised-port-udp` analogously.\r\n\r\nThe code that stops Teku when a port conflict is detected will need attention too.",
